examples: Polygonization is the process of forming polygons from linework which encloses areas. Linework to be formed into polygons must be fully noded – that is, linestrings must not cross and must touch only at endpoints.

entries.meaning: (neologism) Pertaining to a group of individuals, possibly geographically separated from each other, that form temporary or recurring project teams.
examples: The noded philosophy is also about flexibility and efficiency in collaboration, especially among people who are geographically far apart.
